Former Senate President and People’s Democratic Party (PDP) presidential aspirant, Anyim Pius Anyim, has said that he has the clear and detailed knowledge to solve the incessant challenges facing Nigeria. He said that with his 33 years in the government of the country and the detailed knowledge gotten after traversing all states of the country, he is the right person to meet the needs of Nigerians.   Seven years after, UK recovers $23m Abacha loot     Power, democracy and magnanimity     Sanwo-Olu’s second term and MURIC’s Jaguda logic   Anyim stayed this when he visited Niger state PDP delegates at the party Secretariat in Minna on Friday. He said that as the engine room of Jonathan’s administration, he has clarity of the solutions to the Nation’s challenges. “If we enthrone the wrong leaders like the current All Progressives Congress (APC) government, then we will have everything wrong. But, if we choose the right leaders like the PDP with vision, then everything will get better. “I have been in the Presidency for 33 years, I have clear and detailed knowledge of the country after I transverse all the States. I did not just get up to run because I am a politician; I got up to fill a vacuum to meet a need. Our country needs to be freed. I want to bring 2015 back, the unexecuted plans and advance it because, there were some viable projects that during President Goodluck Jonathan’s tenure, we intended to execute for the second term but unfortunately we could not get the second term.